songs.title: Came Up (Original Version)
songs.lyrics:
[Intro: Post Malone]
Ooh
Yeah yeah, yeah yeah, yeah yeah
Yeah yeah, yeah yeah, yeah

[Chorus: Post Malone]
Bitch I came up and I don't know
I don't know where I go tomorrow
Bitch I came up and I don't know
I don't know what's gonna come tomorrow
Bitch I came up and I don't know
I don't know where I go tomorrow
Bitch I came up and I don't know
I don't know what's gonna come tomorrow, yeah

[Verse 1: Key! & Post Malone]
I don't even worry about tomorrow
It might be some money, it might be a ho, okay
I don't where I'mma be tomorrow
Might be countin' dough, in bed with your ho
Okay, her nose keep runnin' and the money keep comin', hey
I'mma keep ballin', hey, Rucker Park Spalding, hey (Park Spalding)
Carefree, I've been living carefree (Carefree)
So much kush in the air, we can barely even breathe, ay
I rarely worry about things I don't know (Don't know)
You say I'm living wrong, you ain't wrong, money long, ay (Money long ay)
So think about it, it ain't nothin' I don't know
All the money that I saw, I don't think I'm ever wrong, ay

[Chorus: Post Malone]
Bitch I came up and I don't know
I don't know where I go tomorrow
Bitch I came up and I don't know
I don't know what's gonna come tomorrow
Bitch I came up and I don't know
I don't know where I go tomorrow
Bitch I came up and I don't know
I don't know what's gonna come tomorrow, yeah

[Verse 2: Post Malone]
Don't bother, bitch don't bother
I just left the mall balling hard like Jordan (Swish)
Out in Fairfax, I was smoking Marlboro
Bitch we so high, bitch I'm high as Ayatollah (Woo)
Bitch I'm three high, bitch I'm high as Ayatollah
She don't want that white coca', I ain't talkin' soda
Bitch ask me, "Do you love me?", I'm like, "What I told ya?"
As I woke up I was smoking on that strong again
That forty keep it funky, I keep it funky (Funky)
Man, I'm smoking on that potent, that's unimportant (Potent)
I just wanted her to fuck me, need her to fuck me (Fuck me)
And she just want all of my money, all my fucking money (Money, money)

[Chorus: Post Malone]
Bitch I came up and I don't know
I don't know where I go tomorrow
Bitch I came up and I don't know
I don't know what's gonna come tomorrow
Bitch I came up and I don't know
I don't know where I go tomorrow
Bitch I came up and I don't know
I don't know what's gonna come tomorrow, yeah

[Outro: Post Malone]
Hey, bitch is somethin' else, what
This bitch is somethin' else, yeah
This bitch is somethin' else, yeah
Man, this life is somethin' else, yeah
